{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1773483365397,"sessionID":"ses_314277d05ffehFsuzTPHpcve3c","part":{"id":"prt_cebd891a3001tzNZXWJt6iK2Ii","sessionID":"ses_314277d05ffehFsuzTPHpcve3c","messageID":"msg_cebd8833d001lRt4k5GvRu6blf","type":"tool","callID":"toolu_vrtx_01Uxkm3Kz8fKAtKF29abJ9DZ","tool":"read","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/fulgidus/Documents/wombo-combo-worktrees/token-cli/AGENTS.md"},"output":"<path>/home/fulgidus/Documents/wombo-combo-worktrees/token-cli/AGENTS.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>1: # AGENTS.md — Instructions for AI agents working on wombo-combo\n2: \n3: This file is for AI coding agents operating **on the wombo-combo codebase itself**.\n4: If you are an agent **using** wombo as a tool in another project, see CONTEXT.md instead.\n5: \n6: ---\n7: \n8: ## HARD CONSTRAINTS\n9: \n10: These are non-negotiable. Violating any of them will break the development workflow.\n11: \n12: ### 1. Always use `bun dev`, never the global binary\n13: \n14: ```\n15: # CORRECT — runs local source directly\n16: bun dev <command> [args...]\n17: \n18: # WRONG — runs the globally installed (possibly stale) binary\n19: wombo <command> [args...]\n20: ```\n21: \n22: **Why:** wombo is dogfooded — we develop it using itself. The global binary is a\n23: snapshot from the last release. If you use it, you're testing old code, not your\n24: changes. `bun dev` runs `bun src/index.ts` which executes the current working tree.\n25: \n26: **Examples:**\n27: ```sh\n28: bun dev help\n29: bun dev tasks list\n30: bun dev tasks add my-feat \"My Feature\" --priority high\n31: bun dev launch --dry-run --all-ready\n32: bun dev init --force\n33: ```\n34: \n35: ### 2. Never publish to npm\n36: \n37: Distribution is GitHub-only. Users install via:\n38: ```sh\n39: bun install -g github:fulgidus/wombo\n40: ```\n41: Do not add `publishConfig`, do not run `npm publish`, do not add `.npmrc`.\n42: \n43: ### 3. Keep bun.lock committed\n44: \n45: The lockfile is committed for reproducible installs from GitHub. Always commit\n46: `bun.lock` after adding/removing/updating dependencies.\n47: \n48: ### 4. Do not commit user artifacts\n49: \n50: All wombo-combo user artifacts live under `.wombo-combo/` (config, tasks, archive,\n51: state, logs, history). This directory is gitignored.\n52: \n53: The template at `src/templates/tasks.yml` is the canonical source for the task\n54: file schema. The root `.wombo-combo/` dir is for local development only.\n55: \n56: ---\n57: \n58: ## Project structure\n59: \n60: ```\n61: wombo/\n62:   package.json              # name: wombo-combo, version in sync with git tags\n63:   src/\n64:     index.ts                # CLI entry point, arg parsing, command routing\n65:     config.ts               # WomboConfig type, defaults, loader, validator\n66:     commands/\n67:       init.ts               # Interactive guided setup (Prompter class)\n68:       launch.ts             # Launch a wave of agents\n69:       resume.ts             # Resume a stopped wave\n70:       status.ts             # Show wave status\n71:       verify.ts             # Build verification\n72:       merge.ts              # Merge verified branches\n73:       retry.ts              # Retry a failed agent\n74:       cleanup.ts            # Remove worktrees and sessions\n75:       tasks/\n76:         list.ts, add.ts, set-status.ts, check.ts, archive.ts, show.ts\n77:     lib/\n78:       tasks.ts              # Task file I/O, types, ensureTasksFile guard\n79:       state.ts              # Wave state persistence\n80:       prompt.ts             # Agent prompt generation\n81:       launcher.ts           # Process spawning\n82:       monitor.ts            # ProcessMonitor\n83:       worktree.ts           # Git worktree management\n84:       merger.ts             # Git merge operations\n85:       verifier.ts           # Build verification logic\n86:       ui.ts                 # Console dashboard\n87:       tui.ts                # neo-blessed TUI\n88:     templates/\n89:       tasks.yml             # Template with full schema docs\n90: ```\n91: \n92: ## User-facing file layout\n93: \n94: All wombo-combo files live under `.wombo-combo/`:\n95: \n96: ```\n97: .wombo-combo/\n98:   config.json     # Project configuration (replaces wombo.json)\n99:   tasks.yml       # Active tasks (replaces .features.yml)\n100:   archive.yml     # Completed/cancelled tasks\n101:   state.json      # Wave state\n102:   logs/           # Agent log files\n103:   history/        # Wave history records\n104: ```\n105: \n106: ## Coding conventions\n107: \n108: - **Runtime:** Bun (not Node). Use Bun APIs where available (`Bun.file()`,\n109:   `Bun.spawn()`, etc.), fall back to Node stdlib when Bun doesn't have a\n110:   direct equivalent.\n111: - **Language:** TypeScript, strict mode. Run `bun run typecheck` to verify.\n112: - **Modules:** ESM only (`\"type\": \"module\"` in package.json). Use `.js`\n113:   extensions in import paths (TypeScript resolves them to `.ts` at runtime in Bun).\n114: - **No external CLI frameworks.** Arg parsing is hand-rolled in `index.ts`.\n115:   This is intentional — it keeps the dependency tree minimal and gives full\n116:   control for agent-readiness features (schema introspection, etc.).\n117: - **YAML library:** `yaml` (v2). Use `YAML.parse()` / `YAML.stringify()`.\n118: - **No npm registry dependencies** for core functionality. `neo-blessed` is\n119:   the only large dependency (TUI). Keep it that way.\n120: \n121: ## Testing and verification\n122: \n123: ```sh\n124: # Type check (no emit)\n125: bun run typecheck\n126: \n127: # Build (outputs to dist/)\n128: bun run build\n129: \n130: # Run any command via dev\n131: bun dev help\n132: bun dev tasks check\n133: ```\n134: \n135: There is no test suite yet. When adding tests, use Bun's built-in test runner\n136: (`bun test`).\n137: \n138: ## Known quirks\n139: \n140: - **Bun readline + piped stdin:** `rl.question()` silently fails after readline\n141:   emits `close`. The `Prompter` class in `src/commands/init.ts` works around\n142:   this using `rl[Symbol.asyncIterator]()` with `process.stdout.write()`.\n143: - **YAML null vs empty array:** `yaml` parses `tasks:` (no items) as `null`,\n144:   not `[]`. `loadTasks()` normalizes this: `parsed.tasks ?? parsed.features ?? null`.\n145: - **`import.meta.dir`:** Gives the directory of the current source file in Bun.\n146:   Used in `src/lib/tasks.ts` to resolve the template path.\n147: \n148: ## Feature backlog\n149: \n150: The active backlog lives in `.wombo-combo/tasks.yml` (local, gitignored). Use\n151: `bun dev tasks list` to see it. The canonical template is at\n152: `src/templates/tasks.yml`.\n153: \n154: ## Making changes\n155: \n156: 1. **Check the backlog:** `bun dev tasks list`\n157: 2. **Pick a feature/subtask:** `bun dev tasks show <id>`\n158: 3. **Mark it in-progress:** `bun dev tasks set-status <id> in_progress`\n159: 4. **Implement the change**\n160: 5. **Typecheck:** `bun run typecheck`\n161: 6. **Build:** `bun run build`\n162: 7. **Test manually:** `bun dev <relevant-command>`\n163: 8. **Mark done:** `bun dev tasks set-status <id> done`\n164: 9. **Commit** with a conventional commit message referencing the feature ID\n165: \n166: ## Version and release\n167: \n168: - Current version is in `package.json` → `\"version\"` field.\n169: - Git tags must match: tag `v0.1.0` ↔ `\"version\": \"0.1.0\"`.\n170: - **When creating a git tag, ALWAYS update `package.json` `\"version\"` first,\n171:   commit the bump, then tag that commit.** Never tag without bumping the\n172:   version — they must stay in sync.\n173: - Release workflow (when implemented) triggers on `v*` tag push to main.\n\n(End of file - total 173 lines)\n</content>","title":"AGENTS.md","metadata":{"preview":"# AGENTS.md — Instructions for AI agents working on wombo-combo\n\nThis file is for AI coding agents operating **on the wombo-combo codebase itself**.\nIf you are an agent **using** wombo as a tool in another project, see CONTEXT.md instead.\n\n---\n\n## HARD CONSTRAINTS\n\nThese are non-negotiable. Violating any of them will break the development workflow.\n\n### 1. Always use `bun dev`, never the global binary\n\n```\n# CORRECT — runs local source directly\nbun dev <command> [args...]\n\n# WRONG — runs the globally installed (possibly stale) binary\nwombo <command> [args...]\n```","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"time":{"start":1773483365389,"end":1773483365396}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1773483365916,"sessionID":"ses_314277d05ffehFsuzTPHpcve3c","part":{"id":"prt_cebd8940f001NtqBfrtRlTcekq","sessionID":"ses_314277d05ffehFsuzTPHpcve3c","messageID":"msg_cebd8833d001lRt4k5GvRu6blf","type":"tool","callID":"toolu_vrtx_019Bo2T2CMfRQWdjrHqs6Ysw","tool":"read","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/fulgidus/Documents/wombo-combo-worktrees/token-cli/src/index.ts"},"output":"<path>/home/fulgidus/Documents/wombo-combo-worktrees/token-cli/src/index.ts</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>1: #!/usr/bin/env bun\n2: /**\n3:  * index.ts — CLI entry point for the wombo-combo agent orchestration system.\n4:  *\n5:  * Every command has a short alias (e.g., woco i = woco init, woco t ls = woco tasks list).\n6:  *\n7:  * Usage:\n8:  *   woco init                                         (alias: i)\n9:  *   woco launch --top-priority 3                      (alias: l)\n10:  *   woco launch --quickest-wins 5\n11:  *   woco launch --priority high\n12:  *   woco launch --difficulty easy\n13:  *   woco launch --tasks \"feat-a,feat-b\"\n14:  *   woco launch --all-ready\n15:  *   woco launch ... --max-concurrent 3 --model \"anthropic/claude-sonnet-4-20250514\"\n16:  *   woco launch ... --interactive\n17:  *   woco resume                                       (alias: r)\n18:  *   woco status                                       (alias: s)\n19:  *   woco verify [feature-id]                          (alias: v)\n20:  *   woco merge [feature-id]                           (alias: m)\n21:  *   woco retry <feature-id>                           (alias: re)\n22:  *   woco abort <feature-id> [--requeue] [--output json]  (alias: a)\n23:  *   woco logs <feature-id> [--tail N] [--follow]      (alias: lo)\n24:  *   woco cleanup                                      (alias: c)\n25:  *   woco history [wave-id] [--output json]            (alias: h)\n26:  *   woco tasks list [--status <s>] [--priority <p>]   (alias: t ls)\n27:  *   woco tasks add <id> <title> [options]             (alias: t a)\n28:  *   woco tasks set-status <task-id> <status>          (alias: t ss)\n29:  *   woco tasks set-priority <task-id> <priority>      (alias: t sp)\n30:  *   woco tasks set-difficulty <task-id> <difficulty>   (alias: t sd)\n31:  *   woco tasks check                                  (alias: t ch)\n32:  *   woco tasks archive [task-id] [--dry-run]          (alias: t ar)\n33:  *   woco tasks show <task-id>                         (alias: t sh)\n34:  *   woco tasks graph [--ascii] [--mermaid]            (alias: t g)\n35:  *   woco completion <bash|zsh|fish>                   (alias: comp)\n36:  *   woco tui                                          (default when no args)\n37:  *   woco help                                         (alias: -h, --help)\n38:  *   woco version\n39:  *   woco -v\n40:  */\n41: \n42: import { resolve } from \"node:path\";\n43: import { existsSync, readFileSync } from \"node:fs\";\n44: import { loadConfig, validateConfig } from \"./config.js\";\n45: import { loadState, saveState } from \"./lib/state.js\";\n46: \n47: // ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n48: // Dev-mode guard: warn if running the global binary inside the wombo-combo repo\n49: // ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n50: \n51: function checkDevModeGuard(): void {\n52:   const cwd = process.cwd();\n53:   const pkgPath = resolve(cwd, \"package.json\");\n54: \n55:   // Are we inside the wombo-combo repo?\n56:   if (!existsSync(pkgPath)) return;\n57: \n58:   let pkgName: string | undefined;\n59:   try {\n60:     const raw = readFileSync(pkgPath, \"utf-8\");\n61:     pkgName = JSON.parse(raw).name;\n62:   } catch {\n63:     return;\n64:   }\n65:   if (pkgName !== \"wombo-combo\") return;\n66: \n67:   // We're in the wombo-combo repo. Is the source being run from a different location?\n68:   // import.meta.dir = directory of THIS file (index.ts). If it's under cwd,\n69:   // we're running local source (bun dev). If it's elsewhere (e.g. ~/.bun/install),\n70:   // we're running the globally installed binary.\n71:   const sourceDir = resolve(import.meta.dir);\n72:   const projectSrc = resolve(cwd, \"src\");\n73: \n74:   if (!sourceDir.startsWith(projectSrc)) {\n75:     console.warn(\n76:       \"\\x1b[33m[WARNING]\\x1b[0m You are running the globally installed woco binary \" +\n77:       \"inside the wombo-combo repo.\\n\" +\n78:       \"  Use \\x1b[1mbun dev <command>\\x1b[0m instead to run from local source.\\n\" +\n79:       \"  See AGENTS.md for details.\\n\"\n80:     );\n81:   }\n82: }\n83: \n84: import { cmdInit } from \"./commands/init.js\";\n85: import { cmdLaunch } from \"./commands/launch.js\";\n86: import { cmdResume } from \"./commands/resume.js\";\n87: import { cmdStatus } from \"./commands/status.js\";\n88: import { cmdVerify } from \"./commands/verify.js\";\n89: import { cmdMerge } from \"./commands/merge.js\";\n90: import { cmdRetry } from \"./commands/retry.js\";\n91: import { cmdCleanup } from \"./commands/cleanup.js\";\n92: import { cmdAbort } from \"./commands/abort.js\";\n93: import { cmdLogs } from \"./commands/logs.js\";\n94: import { cmdUpgrade } from \"./commands/upgrade.js\";\n95: import { cmdHistory } from \"./commands/history.js\";\n96: import { cmdCompletion } from \"./commands/completion.js\";\n97: import { cmdTasksList } from \"./commands/tasks/list.js\";\n98: import { cmdTasksAdd } from \"./commands/tasks/add.js\";\n99: import { cmdTasksSetStatus } from \"./commands/tasks/set-status.js\";\n100: import { cmdTasksSetPriority } from \"./commands/tasks/set-priority.js\";\n101: import { cmdTasksSetDifficulty } from \"./commands/tasks/set-difficulty.js\";\n102: import { cmdTasksCheck } from \"./commands/tasks/check.js\";\n103: import { cmdTasksArchive } from \"./commands/tasks/archive.js\";\n104: import { cmdTasksShow } from \"./commands/tasks/show.js\";\n105: import { cmdTasksGraph } from \"./commands/tasks/graph.js\";\n106: import { cmdTui } from \"./commands/tui.js\";\n107: import { handleQuestSubcommand } from \"./commands/quest.js\";\n108: import { cmdGenesis } from \"./commands/genesis.js\";\n109: \n110: import { ensureTasksFile } from \"./lib/tasks.js\";\n111: import type { Priority, Difficulty, FeatureStatus } from \"./lib/tasks.js\";\n112: import type { QuestHitlMode } from \"./lib/quest.js\";\n113: import { resolveOutputFormat, outputError, type OutputFormat } from \"./lib/output.js\";\n114: import { validateId, validateText, validateBranchName, validateDuration, assertValid } from \"./lib/validate.js\";\n115: import { findCommandDef, commandToSchema, allCommandSchemas } from \"./lib/schema.js\";\n116: import { buildToonSpec, renderToonLegend } from \"./lib/toon-spec.js\";\n117: \n118: // ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n119: // Types\n120: // ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n121: \n122: export interface CLIArgs {\n123:   command: string;\n124:   subcommand?: string;\n125:   // Selection options (launch)\n126:   topPriority?: number;\n127:   quickestWins?: number;\n128:   priority?: Priority;\n129:   difficulty?: Difficulty;\n130:   tasks?: string[];\n131:   allReady?: boolean;\n132:   // Launch / runtime options\n133:   maxConcurrent?: number;\n134:   model?: string;\n135:   interactive: boolean;\n136:   dryRun: boolean;\n137:   baseBranch?: string;\n138:   maxRetries?: number;\n139:   noTui: boolean;\n140:   autoPush: boolean;\n141:   // Abort options\n142:   requeue: boolean;\n143:   // General\n144:   featureId?: string;\n145:   force: boolean;\n146:   // Output format\n147:   outputFmt: OutputFormat;\n148:   // Upgrade options\n149:   checkOnly: boolean;\n150:   tag?: string;\n151:   // Features subcommand extras\n152:   status?: string;\n153:   ready?: boolean;\n154:   includeArchive?: boolean;\n155:   title?: string;\n156:   description?: string;\n157:   effort?: string;\n158:   dependsOn?: string[];\n159:   // Logs options\n160:   tail?: number;\n161:   follow?: boolean;\n162:   // Compact output\n163:   fields?: string[];\n164:   // Graph options\n165:   ascii?: boolean;\n166:   mermaidRaw?: boolean;\n167:   graphSubtasks?: boolean;\n168:   // Browser verification\n169:   browser?: boolean;\n170:   // TDD verification\n171:   skipTests?: boolean;\n172:   strictTdd?: boolean;\n173:   // Agent selection (per-task override)\n174:   agent?: string;\n175:   // Quest-specific options\n176:   goal?: string;\n177:   hitlMode?: QuestHitlMode;\n178:   /** Quest ID to scope a launch to (--quest <id>) */\n179:   questId?: string;\n180:   /** Tech stack description for genesis (--tech-stack) */\n181:   techStack?: string;\n182:   /** Constraints for genesis (--constraint, can be repeated) */\n183:   genesisConstraints?: string[];\n184:   /** Skip TUI review (--no-tui for genesis) */\n185:   genesisNoTui?: boolean;\n186: }\n187: \n188: // ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n189: // Command & Subcommand Aliases\n190: // ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n191: \n192: /** Map of short aliases → canonical top-level command names. */\n193: export const COMMAND_ALIASES: Record<string, string> = {\n194:   i: \"init\",\n195:   l: \"launch\",\n196:   r: \"resume\",\n197:   s: \"status\",\n198:   v: \"verify\",\n199:   m: \"merge\",\n200:   re: \"retry\",\n201:   a: \"abort\",\n202:   c: \"cleanup\",\n203:   h: \"history\",\n204:   lo: \"logs\",\n205:   t: \"tasks\",\n206:   features: \"tasks\", // backward-compat full-word alias\n207:   q: \"quest\",\n208:   g: \"genesis\",\n209:   u: \"upgrade\",\n210:   d: \"describe\",\n211:   comp: \"completion\",\n212:   tui: \"tui\",\n213: };\n214: \n215: /** Map of short aliases → canonical tasks subcommand names. */\n216: export const SUBCOMMAND_ALIASES: Record<string, string> = {\n217:   ls: \"list\",\n218:   a: \"add\",\n219:   ss: \"set-status\",\n220:   sp: \"set-priority\",\n221:   sd: \"set-difficulty\",\n222:   ch: \"check\",\n223:   validate: \"check\", // backward-compat full-word alias\n224:   ar: \"archive\",\n225:   sh: \"show\",\n226:   g: \"graph\",\n227: };\n228: \n229: /** Map of short aliases → canonical quest subcommand names. */\n230: export const QUEST_SUBCOMMAND_ALIASES: Record<string, string> = {\n231:   c: \"create\",\n232:   ls: \"list\",\n233:   sh: \"show\",\n234:   pl: \"plan\",\n235:   a: \"activate\",\n236:   p: \"pause\",\n237:   co: \"complete\",\n238:   ab: \"abandon\",\n239: };\n240: \n241: // ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n242: // Arg Parsing\n243: // ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n244: \n245: export function parseArgs(argv: string[]): CLIArgs {\n246:   const args = argv.slice(2); // skip 'bun' and script path\n247:   const result: CLIArgs = {\n248:     command: args[0] || \"tui\",\n249:     interactive: false,\n250:     dryRun: false,\n251:     noTui: false,\n252:     autoPush: false,\n253:     requeue: false,\n254:     force: false,\n255:     checkOnly: false,\n256:     outputFmt: resolveOutputFormat(undefined), // auto-detect until --output overrides\n257:   };\n258: \n259:   // Resolve top-level command alias (e.g., \"i\" → \"init\", \"t\" → \"tasks\")\n260:   result.command = COMMAND_ALIASES[result.command] ?? result.command;\n261: \n262:   // If the command is \"tasks\", treat the second positional as the subcommand\n263:   let startIdx = 1;\n264:   if (result.command === \"tasks\") {\n265:     result.subcommand = args[1] || \"list\";\n266:     // Resolve subcommand alias (e.g., \"ls\" → \"list\", \"ss\" → \"set-status\")\n267:     result.subcommand = SUBCOMMAND_ALIASES[result.subcommand] ?? result.subcommand;\n268:     startIdx = 2;\n269:   } else if (result.command === \"quest\") {\n270:     result.subcommand = args[1] || \"list\";\n271:     // Resolve quest subcommand alias (e.g., \"c\" → \"create\", \"sh\" → \"show\")\n272:     result.subcommand = QUEST_SUBCOMMAND_ALIASES[result.subcommand] ?? result.subcommand;\n273:     startIdx = 2;\n274:   }\n275: \n276:   for (let i = startIdx; i < args.length; i++) {\n277:     const arg = args[i];\n278: \n279:     // Helper: consume the next argument, or exit with a clear error\n280:     function requireValue(flag: string): string {\n281:       if (i + 1 >= args.length) {\n282:         outputError(result.outputFmt, `Flag ${flag} requires a value.`);\n283:       }\n284:       return args[++i];\n285:     }\n286: \n287:     switch (arg) {\n288:       // --- Selection options ---\n289:       case \"--top-priority\":\n290:         result.topPriority = parseInt(requireValue(arg), 10);\n291:         break;\n292:       case \"--quickest-wins\":\n293:         result.quickestWins = parseInt(requireValue(arg), 10);\n294:         break;\n295:       case \"--priority\":\n296:         result.priority = requireValue(arg) as Priority;\n297:         break;\n298:       case \"--difficulty\":\n299:         result.difficulty = requireValue(arg) as Difficulty;\n300:         break;\n301:       case \"--tasks\":\n302:       case \"--features\": // backward-compat alias\n303:         result.tasks = requireValue(arg).split(\",\").map((s) => s.trim());\n304:         break;\n305:       case \"--all-ready\":\n306:         result.allReady = true;\n307:         break;\n308: \n309:       // --- Launch / runtime options ---\n310:       case \"--max-concurrent\":\n311:         result.maxConcurrent = parseInt(requireValue(arg), 10);\n312:         break;\n313:       case \"--model\":\n314:       case \"-m\":\n315:         result.model = requireValue(arg);\n316:         break;\n317:       case \"--interactive\":\n318:         result.interactive = true;\n319:         break;\n320:       case \"--dry-run\":\n321:         result.dryRun = true;\n322:         break;\n323:       case \"--no-tui\":\n324:         result.noTui = true;\n325:         break;\n326:       case \"--auto-push\":\n327:         result.autoPush = true;\n328:         break;\n329:       case \"--requeue\":\n330:         result.requeue = true;\n331:         break;\n332:       case \"--base-branch\":\n333:         result.baseBranch = requireValue(arg);\n334:         break;\n335:       case \"--max-retries\":\n336:         result.maxRetries = parseInt(requireValue(arg), 10);\n337:         break;\n338: \n339:       // --- General flags ---\n340:       case \"--force\":\n341:         result.force = true;\n342:         break;\n343:       case \"--check\":\n344:         result.checkOnly = true;\n345:         break;\n346:       case \"--tag\":\n347:       case \"--release\":\n348:         result.tag = requireValue(arg);\n349:         break;\n350:       case \"--output\":\n351:       case \"-o\":\n352:         result.outputFmt = resolveOutputFormat(requireValue(arg));\n353:         break;\n354: \n355:       // --- Tasks subcommand options ---\n356:       case \"--status\":\n357:         result.status = requireValue(arg);\n358:         break;\n359:       case \"--ready\":\n360:         result.ready = true;\n361:         break;\n362:       case \"--include-archive\":\n363:         result.includeArchive = true;\n364:         break;\n365:       case \"--title\":\n366:         result.title = requireValue(arg);\n367:         break;\n368:       case \"--description\":\n369:       case \"--desc\":\n370:         result.description = requireValue(arg);\n371:         break;\n372:       case \"--effort\":\n373:         result.effort = requireValue(arg);\n374:         break;\n375:       case \"--depends-on\":\n376:         result.dependsOn = requireValue(arg).split(\",\").map((s) => s.trim());\n377:         break;\n378:       case \"--fields\":\n379:         result.fields = requireValue(arg).split(\",\").map((s) => s.trim());\n380:         break;\n381: \n382:       // --- Graph options ---\n383:       case \"--ascii\":\n384:         result.ascii = true;\n385:         break;\n386:       case \"--mermaid\":\n387:         result.mermaidRaw = true;\n388:         break;\n389:       case \"--subtasks\":\n390:         result.graphSubtasks = true;\n391:         break;\n392: \n393:       // --- Logs options ---\n394:       case \"--tail\":\n395:         result.tail = parseInt(requireValue(arg), 10);\n396:         break;\n397:       case \"--follow\":\n398:       case \"-f\":\n399:         result.follow = true;\n400:         break;\n401: \n402:       // --- Browser verification ---\n403:       case \"--browser\":\n404:         result.browser = true;\n405:         break;\n406: \n407:       // --- TDD verification ---\n408:       case \"--skip-tests\":\n409:         result.skipTests = true;\n410:         break;\n411:       case \"--strict-tdd\":\n412:         result.strictTdd = true;\n413:         break;\n414: \n415:       // --- Agent selection ---\n416:       case \"--agent\":\n417:         result.agent = requireValue(arg);\n418:         break;\n419: \n420:       // --- Quest-specific options ---\n421:       case \"--goal\":\n422:         result.goal = requireValue(arg);\n423:         break;\n424:       case \"--hitl\":\n425:         result.hitlMode = requireValue(arg) as QuestHitlMode;\n426:         break;\n427:       case \"--quest\":\n428:         result.questId = requireValue(arg);\n429:         break;\n430: \n431:       // --- Genesis-specific options ---\n432:       case \"--tech-stack\":\n433:         result.techStack = requireValue(arg);\n434:         break;\n435:       case \"--constraint\":\n436:         if (!result.genesisConstraints) result.genesisConstraints = [];\n437:         result.genesisConstraints.push(requireValue(arg));\n438:         break;\n439: \n440:       // --- Positional (feature-id, title for add, etc.) ---\n441:       default:\n442:         if (!arg.startsWith(\"-\")) {\n443:           if (!result.featureId) {\n444:             result.featureId = arg;\n445:           } else if (!result.title) {\n446:             result.title = arg;\n447:           }\n448:         }\n449:         break;\n450:     }\n451:   }\n452: \n453:   return result;\n454: }\n455: \n456: // ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n457: // Help\n458: // ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n459: \n460: function cmdHelp(): void {\n461:   console.log(`\n462: wombo-combo — AI Agent Orchestration System\n463: \n464:   WOMBO COMBO! Parallel feature development with AI agents.\n465: \n466: Commands:                        (alias)\n467:   init                           (i)     Generate .wombo-combo/config.json in the current project\n468:   launch                         (l)     Launch a wave of agents to implement features\n469:   resume                         (r)     Resume a previously stopped wave\n470:   status                         (s)     Show the status of the current wave\n471:   verify                         (v)     Run build verification on completed agents\n472:   merge                          (m)     Merge verified branches into the base branch\n473:   retry                          (re)    Retry a failed agent\n474:   abort                          (a)     Kill a single running agent (--requeue to return to queue)\n475:   logs                           (lo)    Pretty-print agent logs for a feature\n476:   cleanup                        (c)     Remove all wave worktrees and multiplexer sessions\n477:   history                        (h)     List/view past wave results (stored in .wombo-combo/history/)\n478:   tasks                          (t)     Manage tasks file (see below; 'features' also accepted)\n479:   quest                          (q)     Manage quests (scoped missions; see below)\n480:   genesis                        (g)     Run genesis planner (project-level decomposition into quests)\n481:   tui                                    Interactive TUI: browse tasks, select, launch, monitor\n482:   upgrade                        (u)     Check for updates and upgrade wombo-combo\n483:   describe                       (d)     Emit JSON schema or TOON legend (--output toon)\n484:   completion                     (comp)  Generate shell completions (bash, zsh, fish)\n485:   version                                Print version and exit\n486:   help                                   Show this help\n487: \n488: Tasks Subcommands:               (alias)\n489:   tasks list                     (ls)    List tasks (--status, --priority, --difficulty, --ready, --include-archive)\n490:   tasks add <id> <title>         (a)     Add a new task (--desc, --priority, --difficulty, --effort, --depends-on)\n491:   tasks set-status <id> <s>      (ss)    Change a task's status\n492:   tasks set-priority <id> <p>    (sp)    Change a task's priority (critical/high/medium/low/wishlist)\n493:   tasks set-difficulty <id> <d>  (sd)    Change a task's difficulty (trivial/easy/medium/hard/very_hard)\n494:   tasks check                    (ch)    Validate tasks file (schema, deps, duplicates, cycles)\n495:   tasks archive [id]             (ar)    Move done/cancelled to archive (--dry-run)\n496:   tasks show <id>                (sh)    Show task details\n497:   tasks graph                    (g)     Visualize dependency graph (--ascii, --mermaid, --subtasks)\n498: \n499: Quest Subcommands:               (alias)\n500:   quest create <id> \"Title\"      (c)     Create a new quest (--goal, --priority, --difficulty, --hitl)\n501:   quest list                     (ls)    List all quests (--status to filter)\n502:   quest show <id>                (sh)    Show quest details\n503:   quest activate <id>            (a)     Activate a quest (creates branch, sets status to active)\n504:   quest pause <id>               (p)     Pause an active/planning quest\n505:   quest complete <id>            (co)    Complete quest (merges branch into base; --force to skip merge)\n506:   quest abandon <id>              (ab)    Abandon quest without merging (--force to delete branch)\n507: \n508: Genesis Options:\n509:   --tech-stack <text>      Describe the tech stack (e.g., \"React, Node, Postgres\")\n510:   --constraint <text>      Add a constraint (can be repeated: --constraint \"...\" --constraint \"...\")\n511:   --model <model>          Model override for the genesis planner agent\n512:   --no-tui                 Skip interactive review, auto-approve all quests\n513:   --dry-run                Show proposed quests without creating them\n514: \n515: Selection Options (for launch):\n516:   --top-priority N         Select top N tasks by priority\n517:   --quickest-wins N        Select N tasks with lowest effort\n518:   --priority <level>       Filter by priority (critical/high/medium/low/wishlist)\n519:   --difficulty <level>     Filter by difficulty (trivial/easy/medium/hard/very_hard)\n520:   --tasks \"id1,id2\"        Select specific tasks by ID (--features also accepted)\n521:   --all-ready              Select all tasks whose dependencies are met\n522: \n523: Launch Options:\n524:   --max-concurrent N       Max agents running in parallel (default: from config)\n525:   --model <model>          Model to use (e.g., \"anthropic/claude-sonnet-4-20250514\")\n526:   --interactive            Use multiplexer (dmux/tmux) TUI mode instead of headless\n527:   --no-tui                 Headless mode without neo-blessed TUI (periodic console dashboard)\n528:   --auto-push              Push base branch to remote after all merges complete\n529:   --dry-run                Show what would be launched without launching\n530:   --base-branch <branch>   Base branch (default: from config)\n531:   --max-retries N          Max retries per agent (default: from config)\n532:   --browser                Enable browser-based verification (run after build passes)\n533:   --skip-tests             Skip running tests during TDD verification\n534:   --strict-tdd             Strict TDD: fail verification if new files are missing tests\n535:   --agent <name>           Override agent definition for all launched tasks (name without .md extension)\n536:   --quest <id>             Scope launch to a quest (uses quest branch as base, applies quest constraints)\n537: \n538: General:\n539:   --force                  Force overwrite (e.g., for init) / skip prompts (e.g., for upgrade)\n540:   --output <fmt>           Output format: text (default on TTY), json (default when piped), or toon (WOMBO_OUTPUT=toon)\n541:   -o <fmt>                 Alias for --output\n542:   --dry-run                Show what would happen without performing the action\n543:   --fields <list>          Comma-separated fields to include (e.g., id,status,priority)\n544: \n545: Upgrade Options:\n546:   --check                  Only check for updates, don't install\n547:   --tag <tag>              Install a specific version (e.g., v0.1.0)\n548: \n549: Logs Options:\n550:   --tail N                 Show only the last N lines\n551:   --follow, -f             Stream new output as it arrives (like tail -f)\n552: \n553: Aliases (every command has a short form):\n554:   woco i                         woco init\n555:   woco l --all-ready             woco launch --all-ready\n556:   woco t ls                      woco tasks list\n557:   woco t a my-task \"Title\"       woco tasks add my-task \"Title\"\n558:   woco t ss my-task done         woco tasks set-status my-task done\n559:   woco q c my-quest \"Quest\"      woco quest create my-quest \"Quest\" --goal \"...\"\n560:   woco q ls                      woco quest list\n561:   woco q sh my-quest             woco quest show my-quest\n562: \n563: Shell Completion:\n564:   eval \"$(woco completion bash)\"    # Bash: add to ~/.bashrc\n565:   eval \"$(woco completion zsh)\"     # Zsh:  add to ~/.zshrc\n566:   woco completion fish | source     # Fish (or save to ~/.config/fish/completions/woco.fish)\n567: \n568: Examples:\n569:   woco init\n570:   woco launch --quickest-wins 3\n571:   woco launch --priority high --interactive\n572:   woco launch --tasks \"auth-flow,search-api\" --max-concurrent 2\n573:   woco resume\n574:   woco status\n575:   woco verify\n576:   woco merge\n577:   woco retry auth-flow\n578:   woco abort auth-flow\n579:   woco abort auth-flow --requeue\n580:   woco abort auth-flow --output json\n581:   woco logs auth-flow\n582:   woco logs auth-flow --tail 50\n583:   woco logs auth-flow --follow\n584:   woco logs auth-flow --output json\n585:   woco cleanup\n586:   woco tasks list --status ready --priority high\n587:   woco tasks list --fields id,status,priority --output json\n588:   woco tasks add my-task \"My Cool Task\" --priority high --difficulty easy\n589:   woco tasks set-status my-task in-progress\n590:   woco tasks check\n591:   woco tasks archive --dry-run\n592:   woco tasks show my-task\n593:   woco history\n594:   woco history wave-2026-03-12-420\n595:   woco history --output json\n596:   woco describe                           # list all commands as JSON\n597:   woco describe launch                    # describe a specific command\n598:   woco describe tasks add                 # describe a subcommand\n599:   woco describe --output toon             # emit TOON format legend/spec\n600:   woco quest create auth \"Auth Overhaul\" --goal \"Replace basic auth with OAuth2\" --priority high\n601:   woco quest list\n602:   woco quest activate auth\n603:   woco quest complete auth\n604:   woco genesis \"Build a SaaS dashboard with auth, billing, and analytics\"\n605:   woco genesis \"Modernize the frontend\" --tech-stack \"React, TypeScript, Tailwind\"\n606:   woco g \"Add multi-tenant support\" --constraint \"No breaking changes\" --constraint \"Keep backward compat\"\n607:   woco genesis \"...\" --dry-run\n608: `);\n609: }\n610: \n611: // ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n612: // Main\n613: // ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n614: \n615: async function main(): Promise<void> {\n616:   checkDevModeGuard();\n617: \n618:   const PROJECT_ROOT = resolve(process.cwd());\n619:   const args = parseArgs(process.argv);\n620: \n621:   // -----------------------------------------------------------------------\n622:   // Input validation at the CLI boundary\n623:   // -----------------------------------------------------------------------\n624:   if (args.featureId) {\n625:     assertValid(validateId(args.featureId, \"feature ID\"));\n626:   }\n627:   if (args.title) {\n628:     assertValid(validateText(args.title, \"title\"));\n629:   }\n630:   if (args.description) {\n631:     assertValid(validateText(args.description, \"description\"));\n632:   }\n633:   if (args.baseBranch) {\n634:     assertValid(validateBranchName(args.baseBranch, \"base branch\"));\n635:   }\n636:   if (args.effort) {\n637:     assertValid(validateDuration(args.effort, \"effort\"));\n638:   }\n639:   if (args.tasks) {\n640:     for (const fid of args.tasks) {\n641:       assertValid(validateId(fid, \"task ID in --tasks\"));\n642:     }\n643:   }\n644:   if (args.dependsOn) {\n645:     for (const dep of args.dependsOn) {\n646:       assertValid(validateId(dep, \"dependency ID in --depends-on\"));\n647:     }\n648:   }\n649: \n650:   // Validate numeric args are not NaN\n651:   const numericArgs: [string, number | undefined][] = [\n652:     [\"--top-priority\", args.topPriority],\n653:     [\"--quickest-wins\", args.quickestWins],\n654:     [\"--max-concurrent\", args.maxConcurrent],\n655:     [\"--max-retries\", args.maxRetries],\n656:     [\"--tail\", args.tail],\n657:   ];\n658:   for (const [flag, value] of numericArgs) {\n659:     if (value !== undefined && isNaN(value)) {\n660:       outputError(args.outputFmt, `${flag} requires a numeric value.`);\n661:     }\n662:   }\n663: \n664:   // Commands that don't need config loading\n665:   if (args.command === \"version\" || args.command === \"-v\" || args.command === \"-V\") {\n666:     const pkgPath = resolve(import.meta.dir, \"..\", \"package.json\");\n667:     const pkgFile = Bun.file(pkgPath);\n668:     try {\n669:       const pkg = await pkgFile.json();\n670:       console.log(`wombo-combo ${pkg.version ?? \"(unknown version)\"}`);\n671:     } catch {\n672:       console.log(\"wombo-combo (unknown version)\");\n673:     }\n674:     return;\n675:   }\n676: \n677:   if (args.command === \"help\" || args.command === \"--help\" || args.command === \"-h\") {\n678:     cmdHelp();\n679:     return;\n680:   }\n681: \n682:   if (args.command === \"describe\") {\n683:     // Schema introspection: `woco describe [command]`\n684:     if (args.outputFmt === \"toon\") {\n685:       // Emit TOON format legend — self-describing, cacheable by agents\n686:       const pkgPath = resolve(import.meta.dir, \"..\", \"package.json\");\n687:       let version = \"unknown\";\n688:       try {\n689:         const pkg = await Bun.file(pkgPath).json();\n690:         version = pkg.version ?? \"unknown\";\n691:       } catch {}\n692: \n693:       if (!args.featureId) {\n694:         // Full TOON spec (legend + all commands)\n695:         console.log(renderToonLegend(version));\n696:       } else {\n697:         // JSON structure for the full spec (--output toon with a specific command\n698:         // still emits JSON since TOON is a line-oriented data format, not a schema format)\n699:         const spec = buildToonSpec(version);\n700:         const cmdName = args.title\n701:           ? `${args.featureId} ${args.title}`\n702:           : args.featureId;\n703:         const cmdSpec = spec.commands.find((c) => c.command === cmdName);\n704:         if (!cmdSpec) {\n705:           outputError(args.outputFmt, `Unknown command: \"${cmdName}\". Run 'woco describe --output toon' to see the full TOON spec.`);\n706:           return;\n707:         }\n708:         console.log(JSON.stringify(cmdSpec, null, 2));\n709:       }\n710:       return;\n711:     }\n712: \n713:     if (!args.featureId) {\n714:       // No command specified — list all commands\n715:       console.log(JSON.stringify(allCommandSchemas(), null, 2));\n716:     } else {\n717:       // Describe a specific command. Handle compound names: \"features list\"\n718:       const cmdName = args.title\n719:         ? `${args.featureId} ${args.title}`\n720:         : args.featureId;\n721:       const def = findCommandDef(cmdName);\n722:       if (!def) {\n723:         outputError(args.outputFmt, `Unknown command: \"${cmdName}\". Run 'woco describe' to list all commands.`);\n724:         return;\n725:       }\n726:       console.log(JSON.stringify(commandToSchema(def), null, 2));\n727:     }\n728:     return;\n729:   }\n730: \n731:   if (args.command === \"init\") {\n732:     await cmdInit({ projectRoot: PROJECT_ROOT, force: args.force });\n733:     return;\n734:   }\n735: \n736:   if (args.command === \"upgrade\") {\n737:     await cmdUpgrade({\n738:       force: args.force,\n739:       tag: args.tag,\n740:       checkOnly: args.checkOnly,\n741:     });\n742:     return;\n743:   }\n744: \n745:   if (args.command === \"completion\") {\n746:     cmdCompletion({ shell: args.featureId }); // first positional = shell name\n747:     return;\n748:   }\n749: \n750:   if (args.command === \"logs\") {\n751:     if (!args.featureId) {\n752:       outputError(args.outputFmt, \"Usage: woco logs <feature-id> [--tail N] [--follow] [--output json]\");\n753:       return;\n754:     }\n755:     await cmdLogs({\n756:       projectRoot: PROJECT_ROOT,\n757:       featureId: args.featureId,\n758:       tail: args.tail,\n759:       follow: args.follow,\n760:       outputFmt: args.outputFmt,\n761:     });\n762:     return;\n763:   }\n764: \n765:   // Everything else requires config\n766:   const config = loadConfig(PROJECT_ROOT);\n767:   validateConfig(config);\n768: \n769:   // Commands that operate on the tasks file — ensure it exists first\n770:   const needsTasksFile = new Set([\"launch\", \"resume\", \"verify\", \"retry\", \"tasks\", \"tui\"]);\n771:   if (needsTasksFile.has(args.command)) {\n772:     await ensureTasksFile(PROJECT_ROOT, config);\n773:   }\n774: \n775:   switch (args.command) {\n776:     case \"launch\":\n777:       // Apply browser verification override if --browser flag was passed\n778:       if (args.browser !== undefined) {\n779:         config.browser.enabled = args.browser;\n780:       }\n781:       try {\n782:         await cmdLaunch({\n783:           projectRoot: PROJECT_ROOT,\n784:           config,\n785:           topPriority: args.topPriority,\n786:           quickestWins: args.quickestWins,\n787:           priority: args.priority,\n788:           difficulty: args.difficulty,\n789:           features: args.tasks,\n790:           allReady: args.allReady,\n791:           maxConcurrent: args.maxConcurrent ?? config.defaults.maxConcurrent,\n792:           model: args.model,\n793:           interactive: args.interactive,\n794:           dryRun: args.dryRun,\n795:           baseBranch: args.baseBranch ?? config.baseBranch,\n796:           maxRetries: args.maxRetries ?? config.defaults.maxRetries,\n797:           noTui: args.noTui,\n798:           autoPush: args.autoPush,\n799:           outputFmt: args.outputFmt,\n800:           agent: args.agent,\n801:           questId: args.questId,\n802:         });\n803:       } catch (err: any) {\n804:         outputError(args.outputFmt ?? \"text\", err.message);\n805:       }\n806:       break;\n807: \n808:     case \"resume\":\n809:       await cmdResume({\n810:         projectRoot: PROJECT_ROOT,\n811:         config,\n812:         maxConcurrent: args.maxConcurrent,\n813:         model: args.model,\n814:         interactive: args.interactive,\n815:         noTui: args.noTui,\n816:         autoPush: args.autoPush,\n817:         baseBranch: args.baseBranch,\n818:         maxRetries: args.maxRetries,\n819:         outputFmt: args.outputFmt,\n820:       });\n821:       break;\n822: \n823:     case \"status\":\n824:       await cmdStatus({ projectRoot: PROJECT_ROOT, config, outputFmt: args.outputFmt });\n825:       break;\n826: \n827:     case \"verify\":\n828:       await cmdVerify({\n829:         projectRoot: PROJECT_ROOT,\n830:         config,\n831:         featureId: args.featureId,\n832:         model: args.model,\n833:         maxRetries: args.maxRetries,\n834:         browserVerify: args.browser,\n835:         skipTests: args.skipTests,\n836:         strictTdd: args.strictTdd,\n837:         outputFmt: args.outputFmt,\n838:       });\n839:       break;\n840: \n841:     case \"merge\":\n842:       await cmdMerge({\n843:         projectRoot: PROJECT_ROOT,\n844:         config,\n845:         featureId: args.featureId,\n846:         autoPush: args.autoPush,\n847:         dryRun: args.dryRun,\n848:         model: args.model,\n849:         outputFmt: args.outputFmt,\n850:       });\n851:       break;\n852: \n853:     case \"retry\": {\n854:       if (!args.featureId) {\n855:         outputError(args.outputFmt, \"Usage: woco retry <feature-id>\");\n856:         return;\n857:       }\n858:       await cmdRetry({\n859:         projectRoot: PROJECT_ROOT,\n860:         config,\n861:         featureId: args.featureId,\n862:         model: args.model,\n863:         interactive: args.interactive,\n864:         dryRun: args.dryRun,\n865:         outputFmt: args.outputFmt,\n866:       });\n867:       break;\n868:     }\n869: \n870:     case \"cleanup\":\n871:       await cmdCleanup({ projectRoot: PROJECT_ROOT, config, dryRun: args.dryRun, outputFmt: args.outputFmt });\n872:       break;\n873: \n874:     case \"history\":\n875:       await cmdHistory({\n876:         projectRoot: PROJECT_ROOT,\n877:         config,\n878:         waveId: args.featureId,\n879:         outputFmt: args.outputFmt,\n880:       });\n881:       break;\n882: \n883:     case \"abort\": {\n884:       if (!args.featureId) {\n885:         outputError(args.outputFmt, \"Usage: woco abort <feature-id> [--requeue] [--output json]\");\n886:         return;\n887:       }\n888:       await cmdAbort({\n889:         projectRoot: PROJECT_ROOT,\n890:         config,\n891:         featureId: args.featureId,\n892:         requeue: args.requeue,\n893:         outputFmt: args.outputFmt,\n894:       });\n895:       break;\n896:     }\n897: \n898:     case \"tasks\":\n899:       await handleTasksSubcommand(args, PROJECT_ROOT, config);\n900:       break;\n901: \n902:     case \"quest\":\n903:       await handleQuestSubcommand({\n904:         projectRoot: PROJECT_ROOT,\n905:         config,\n906:         subcommand: args.subcommand ?? \"list\",\n907:         questId: args.featureId,\n908:         title: args.title,\n909:         goal: args.goal,\n910:         priority: args.priority,\n911:         difficulty: args.difficulty,\n912:         hitlMode: args.hitlMode,\n913:         status: args.status,\n914:         agent: args.agent,\n915:         dryRun: args.dryRun,\n916:         force: args.force,\n917:         outputFmt: args.outputFmt,\n918:         fields: args.fields,\n919:       });\n920:       break;\n921: \n922:     case \"genesis\":\n923:       await cmdGenesis({\n924:         projectRoot: PROJECT_ROOT,\n925:         config,\n926:         vision: args.featureId,  // first positional arg is the vision text\n927:         techStack: args.techStack,\n928:         constraints: args.genesisConstraints,\n929:         model: args.model,\n930:         dryRun: args.dryRun,\n931:         noTui: args.noTui,\n932:         outputFmt: args.outputFmt,\n933:       });\n934:       break;\n935: \n936:     case \"tui\":\n937:       await cmdTui({\n938:         projectRoot: PROJECT_ROOT,\n939:         config,\n940:         maxConcurrent: args.maxConcurrent,\n941:         model: args.model,\n942:         baseBranch: args.baseBranch,\n943:         maxRetries: args.maxRetries,\n944:         autoPush: args.autoPush,\n945:         skipTests: args.skipTests,\n946:         strictTdd: args.strictTdd,\n947:         agent: args.agent,\n948:       });\n949:       break;\n950: \n951:     default:\n952:       if (args.outputFmt !== \"text\") {\n953:         outputError(args.outputFmt, `Unknown command: ${args.command}`);\n954:       }\n955:       console.error(`Unknown command: ${args.command}`);\n956:       cmdHelp();\n957:       process.exit(1);\n958:       return;\n959:   }\n960: }\n961: \n962: // ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n963: // Tasks Subcommand Router\n964: // ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n965: \n966: async function handleTasksSubcommand(\n967:   args: CLIArgs,\n968:   projectRoot: string,\n969:   config: import(\"./config.js\").WomboConfig\n970: ): Promise<void> {\n971:   switch (args.subcommand) {\n972:     case \"list\":\n973:       await cmdTasksList({\n974:         projectRoot,\n975:         config,\n976:         status: args.status as FeatureStatus | undefined,\n977:         priority: args.priority,\n978:         difficulty: args.difficulty,\n979:         ready: args.ready,\n980:         includeArchive: args.includeArchive,\n981:         outputFmt: args.outputFmt,\n982:         fields: args.fields,\n983:       });\n984:       break;\n985: \n986:     case \"add\": {\n987:       if (!args.featureId || !args.title) {\n988:         outputError(args.outputFmt, \"Usage: woco tasks add <id> <title> [--desc <desc>] [--priority <p>] [--difficulty <d>] [--effort <e>] [--depends-on <ids>]\");\n989:         return;\n990:       }\n991:       await cmdTasksAdd({\n992:         projectRoot,\n993:         config,\n994:         id: args.featureId,\n995:         title: args.title,\n996:         description: args.description,\n997:         priority: args.priority,\n998:         difficulty: args.difficulty,\n999:         effort: args.effort,\n1000:         dependsOn: args.dependsOn,\n1001:         outputFmt: args.outputFmt,\n1002:         dryRun: args.dryRun,\n1003:       });\n1004:       break;\n1005:     }\n1006: \n1007:     case \"set-status\": {\n1008:       // The new status can come from the second positional (stored in args.title)\n1009:       // or from the --status flag\n1010:       const newStatus = args.title || args.status;\n1011:       if (!args.featureId || !newStatus) {\n1012:         outputError(args.outputFmt, \"Usage: woco tasks set-status <task-id> <status>\");\n1013:         return;\n1014:       }\n1015:       await cmdTasksSetStatus({\n1016:         projectRoot,\n1017:         config,\n1018:         featureId: args.featureId,\n1019:         newStatus,\n1020:         outputFmt: args.outputFmt,\n1021:         dryRun: args.dryRun,\n1022:       });\n1023:       break;\n1024:     }\n1025: \n1026:     case \"set-priority\": {\n1027:       // The new priority can come from the second positional (stored in args.title)\n1028:       // or from the --priority flag\n1029:       const newPriority = args.title || (args.priority as string | undefined);\n1030:       if (!args.featureId || !newPriority) {\n1031:         outputError(args.outputFmt, \"Usage: woco tasks set-priority <task-id> <priority>\");\n1032:         return;\n1033:       }\n1034:       await cmdTasksSetPriority({\n1035:         projectRoot,\n1036:         config,\n1037:         featureId: args.featureId,\n1038:         newPriority,\n1039:         outputFmt: args.outputFmt,\n1040:         dryRun: args.dryRun,\n1041:       });\n1042:       break;\n1043:     }\n1044: \n1045:     case \"set-difficulty\": {\n1046:       // The new difficulty can come from the second positional (stored in args.title)\n1047:       // or from the --difficulty flag\n1048:       const newDifficulty = args.title || (args.difficulty as string | undefined);\n1049:       if (!args.featureId || !newDifficulty) {\n1050:         outputError(args.outputFmt, \"Usage: woco tasks set-difficulty <task-id> <difficulty>\");\n1051:         return;\n1052:       }\n1053:       await cmdTasksSetDifficulty({\n1054:         projectRoot,\n1055:         config,\n1056:         featureId: args.featureId,\n1057:         newDifficulty,\n1058:         outputFmt: args.outputFmt,\n1059:         dryRun: args.dryRun,\n1060:       });\n1061:       break;\n1062:     }\n1063: \n1064:     case \"check\":\n1065:       await cmdTasksCheck({ projectRoot, config, outputFmt: args.outputFmt });\n1066:       break;\n1067: \n1068:     case \"archive\":\n1069:       await cmdTasksArchive({\n1070:         projectRoot,\n1071:         config,\n1072:         featureId: args.featureId,\n1073:         dryRun: args.dryRun,\n1074:         outputFmt: args.outputFmt,\n1075:       });\n1076:       break;\n1077: \n1078:     case \"show\": {\n1079:       if (!args.featureId) {\n1080:         outputError(args.outputFmt, \"Usage: woco tasks show <task-id>\");\n1081:         return;\n1082:       }\n1083:       await cmdTasksShow({\n1084:         projectRoot,\n1085:         config,\n1086:         featureId: args.featureId,\n1087:         outputFmt: args.outputFmt,\n1088:         fields: args.fields,\n1089:       });\n1090:       break;\n1091:     }\n1092: \n1093:     case \"graph\":\n1094:       await cmdTasksGraph({\n1095:         projectRoot,\n1096:         config,\n1097:         status: args.status as FeatureStatus | undefined,\n1098:         ascii: args.ascii,\n1099:         mermaid: args.mermaidRaw,\n1100:         subtasks: args.graphSubtasks,\n1101:         outputFmt: args.outputFmt,\n1102:       });\n1103:       break;\n1104: \n1105:     case \"help\":\n1106:     case \"--help\":\n1107:     case \"-h\":\n1108:       cmdHelp();\n1109:       break;\n1110: \n1111:     default:\n1112:       outputError(args.outputFmt, `Unknown tasks subcommand: ${args.subcommand}. Run 'woco tasks help' or 'woco help' for usage.`);\n1113:       return;\n1114:   }\n1115: }\n1116: \n1117: // ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n1118: // Error Handlers & Entry\n1119: // ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n1120: \n1121: // Global error handlers — prevent silent crashes\n1122: process.on(\"uncaughtException\", (err) => {\n1123:   console.error(`\\n[FATAL] Uncaught exception: ${err.message}`);\n1124:   console.error(err.stack);\n1125:   try {\n1126:     const state = loadState(process.cwd());\n1127:     if (state) saveState(process.cwd(), state);\n1128:   } catch {}\n1129:   process.exit(1);\n1130: });\n1131: \n1132: process.on(\"unhandledRejection\", (reason: any) => {\n1133:   console.error(`\\n[FATAL] Unhandled rejection: ${reason?.message || reason}`);\n1134:   if (reason?.stack) console.error(reason.stack);\n1135:   try {\n1136:     const state = loadState(process.cwd());\n1137:     if (state) saveState(process.cwd(), state);\n1138:   } catch {}\n1139:   process.exit(1);\n1140: });\n1141: \n1142: main().catch((err) => {\n1143:   console.error(\"Fatal error:\", err.message);\n1144:   process.exit(1);\n1145: });\n\n(End of file - total 1145 lines)\n</content>","title":"src/index.ts","metadata":{"preview":"#!/usr/bin/env bun\n/**\n * index.ts — CLI entry point for the wombo-combo agent orchestration system.\n *\n * Every command has a short alias (e.g., woco i = woco init, woco t ls = woco tasks list).\n *\n * Usage:\n *   woco init                                         (alias: i)\n *   woco launch --top-priority 3                      (alias: l)\n *   woco launch --quickest-wins 5\n *   woco launch --priority high\n *   woco launch --difficulty easy\n *   woco launch --tasks \"feat-a,feat-b\"\n *   woco launch --all-ready\n *   woco launch ... --max-concurrent 3 --model \"anthropic/claude-sonnet-4-20250514\"\n *   woco launch ... --interactive\n *   woco resume                                       (alias: r)\n *   woco status                                       (alias: s)\n *   woco verify [feature-id]                          (alias: v)\n *   woco merge [feature-id]             