{"type":"text","timestamp":1773483531579,"sessionID":"ses_314277d05ffehFsuzTPHpcve3c","part":{"id":"prt_cebdb0aeb001W5ftN0augVpKGo","sessionID":"ses_314277d05ffehFsuzTPHpcve3c","messageID":"msg_cebdb02600011HIbN7fcPpdvPp","type":"text","text":"Now let me add the command routing in the main() function. I should add it before the config-requiring commands since it needs config (it uses project root for the JSONL file path). Let me check if it actually requires config:\n\nLooking at the `loadUsageRecords` function, it only needs `projectRoot`. However, looking at the pattern, the `history` command also loads config. Let me add usage similarly — it doesn't strictly need config but for consistency with the existing pattern, I'll handle it after config loading. Actually, looking more carefully, the usage command just needs the project root to find `.wombo-combo/usage.jsonl`. It doesn't need the tasks file. Let me add it as a command that requires config but not the tasks file.","time":{"start":1773483531578,"end":1773483531578}}}
